</it> in similar roles.<p>

By 1987, few racing games existed for the NES, and <it>Rad Racer</it> was seen as Square's answer to <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../910/26910.xml">
Sega's</link></company>
 <it><event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<social_event wordnetid="107288639" confidence="0.8">
<contest wordnetid="107456188" confidence="0.8">
<game wordnetid="100456199" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../098/449098.xml">
Out Run</link></psychological_feature>
</game>
</contest>
</social_event>
</event>
</it>. In <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../635/34635.xml">
1990</link>, Square followed up with an exclusive North American sequel, <it><event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<social_event wordnetid="107288639" confidence="0.8">
<contest wordnetid="107456188" confidence="0.8">
<game wordnetid="100456199" confidence="0.8">
