<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../761/993761.xml">
Rad Racer II</link></psychological_feature>
</game>
</contest>
</social_event>
</event>
</it>. It differed little from the first version, and players considered the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../743/472743.xml">
gameplay</link> inferior;<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> as a result, it was not as successful as the first version.</p>
<p>

The game appeared in an infamous scene in <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../196/936196.xml">
The Wizard</link></movie>
</it>, where Lucas Barton (Jimmy's rival) uses a <artifact wordnetid="100021939" confidence="0.8">
